---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navigation from '../../components/Navigation.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import MobileCallBar from '../../components/MobileCallBar.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import { PHONE_DISPLAY, PHONE_HREF } from '../../data/pricing';

const elements = [
  'A color palette and typography system that fits your business, not a default theme',
  'Consistent layout language across every page, so your site feels like one business, not a stack of stock sections',
  'Voice and tone guidance baked into the copy, so your site sounds like you, not generic marketing filler',
  'Favicon, social share previews (Open Graph images), and other small details that make your brand look finished everywhere it appears online',
];
---

<Layout title="Brand-Aligned Design | Orange County Webworks" description="Cohesive visual identity and design-system work built into every custom website for Orange County, NY businesses.">
  <Navigation />
  <main id="main-content" class="pb-20 md:pb-0">
    <PageHero
      eyebrow="Brand-Aligned Design"
      title="A Site That Actually Looks Like Your Business"
      subtitle="This isn't standalone logo design or a print-collateral package — it's making sure everything about your site (color, type, layout, voice) works together as one consistent identity."
    />

    <div class="text-center -mt-4 mb-8">
      <span class="inline-block rounded-full border border-violet-400/30 bg-slate-900/40 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-bold text-violet-300">
        Included in every package
      </span>
    </div>

    <section class="relative py-8">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          If you already have a logo and brand colors, I build your site around them. If you don't have a formal brand yet, we'll define a simple, consistent visual direction together as part of the build — colors, fonts, and layout style that fit your business and your customers. What's included:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-4 mb-12">
          {elements.map((el) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg class="w-5 h-5 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0 text-violet-400" fill="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 20 20" aria-hidden="true">
                <path fill-rule="evenodd" d="M16.707 5.293a1 1 0 010 1.414l-8 8a1 1 0 01-1.414 0l-4-4a1 1 0 011.414-1.414L8 12.586l7.293-7.293a1 1 0 011.414 0z" clip-rule="evenodd" />
              </svg>
              <span class="text-slate-300">{el}</span>
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>

        <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
          Worth being upfront: this is a design system built into your website, not standalone logo design, print collateral, or brand-strategy consulting as a separate service. If you need a logo designed from scratch, mention it during your consultation and we'll figure out the right path.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-12 text-center">
          <a
            href={PHONE_HREF}
            class="inline-block px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold bg-violet-500/10 border border-violet-400/50 text-violet-300 hover:bg-violet-500/20 hover:border-violet-400 transition-all duration-300 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-violet-400"
          >
            Call {PHONE_DISPLAY}
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
  <Footer />
  <MobileCallBar />
</Layout>
